title: About me
text: You can call me Anh. I am currently a Ph.D. student in the Department of Statistics at the University of Wisconsin, Madison.

title: About me
text:
Previously
Before that I was a M.S. student and taught as a Visisting Assistant Professor in the Department of Statistics at Wake Forest University. There I worked with Dr. Sarah Lotspeich on correcting for missing data for surrogate validation in a clinical setting. I was a math major at Smith College with a minor in Statistics and Data Science.
